        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-3/10_icon.png",
        "description": "10\r\nPunch\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nFist\r\nVerb\r\nPunch\r\nAdjective\r\nBattered\r\nAdverb\r\nPugnaciously\r\nQuestion\r\nNo\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nNo; those opposed will fight \r\ntooth and nail to prevent.\r\nSocial\r\nThis person is looking for a fight.  Given the least \r\nexcuse—say, a failed social check—they will spring \r\nup and suggest a duel.  A successful social check is \r\nneeded to calm them down and get them to return \r\nto the conversation.  Fighting them and losing earns \r\ntheir good will and their \r\n  Attitude toward you \r\nincreases; fighting them and winning, but pulling your \r\nlast punches, gets them to talk with you, but they feel \r\nforced to do so, and you suffer a -2 penalty to social \r\nchecks.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Opponent\r\nContext\r\n  Combat\r\nChoice\r\n  Intimidate\r\nResult\r\n  Turns Hostile\r\nCombat\r\nMelee attacks from your enemies are stronger than \r\nyou’d expect: they apply double their \r\n  Strength \r\nbonus to damage rolls.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nNPC toughs taunt you.  If you ignore them, they step \r\nup their verbal assault.  Although their diatribes \r\nbecome increasingly rude and volatile, and their \r\nthreats specific, they will not be the ones to throw the \r\nfirst punch.  They follow the party until a fight takes \r\nplace, or they are physically prevented from following.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Attack Main\r\nTargeting\r\n  Closest\r\nRole\r\n  Brute\r\nRole Size\r\n  Elite\r\nStance\r\n  Bloodied\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nAn informal fighting club has become quite popular, \r\nbut with its rise has come an increase in supposedly \r\n“accidental” lethality.  Injuries mount, and there \r\nis even rumor that some have been doctoring their \r\nboxing gloves with nails or jagged wood.  The party \r\nis tasked with infiltrating or investigating as they see \r\nfit, and either pulling back the fighting to nonlethal \r\nfriendly bouts, or dissolving the group altogether.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nThe next objective you have is blocked by an NPC who \r\nhas an ulterior motive and reason to protect it from \r\nyou.  They are obstinant in their blockade, and must \r\nultimately be fought or disabled to proceed.\r\n  Reward\r\nA ring that, when tapped as a free action, expands \r\ninto a full-on spiked gauntlet (and back again in the \r\nsame manner).  It automatically succeeds on any skill \r\nchecks made to conceal its true nature, and it inflicts \r\ndamage as a dagger if your rules system does not \r\nhave stats for a spiked gauntlet.  When you roll a \r\n  \r\ncritical failure on an attack roll with the weapon, its \r\nmagic evaporates.\r\n  Penalty\r\nA minor fissure has occurred in a PC’s finger bone on \r\ntheir dominant hand.  It’s not a serious wound, but the \r\npain imposes a -1 penalty on all \r\n  d20 rolls (attack, \r\nskill check) made that involve that hand.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Slay\r\nSub\r\n  Clear\r\n13"
