        "id": "oracle-3-12",
        "oracleSet": 3,
        "number": 12,
        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-3/12_icon.png",
        "description": "12\r\nStack of Books\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nLibrary\r\nVerb\r\nStack\r\nAdjective\r\nStacked\r\nAdverb\r\nThoughtfully\r\nQuestion\r\nNo\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nNo; there are too many options \r\nto consider to select only the \r\nright one.\r\nSocial\r\nThis NPC believes themselves to be supremely \r\ninformed, about any topic that arises.  Their arrogance \r\nis only slightly justified, in that they are certainly \r\nsmart.  You may gather \r\n  1d6 \r\n  rumors from them, \r\nbut their haughtiness makes it tough to tell if they are \r\ntrue.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Asset\r\nContext\r\n  Long Rest\r\nChoice\r\n  Mislead\r\nResult\r\n  Answers Willingly\r\nCombat\r\nEach time an enemy spellcaster casts magic, roll a \r\n  \r\nd6; on a 6, that use does not count as expended.  If \r\nyour enemies do not include spellcasters, one of your \r\nfoes turns out to have arcane magical abilities.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nA book salesperson approaches; most of their wares \r\nare novels or obviously faked copies of uninteresting \r\nworks, but amongst their tomes is a spellbook that the \r\nsalesperson has not noticed.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Flee\r\nTargeting\r\n  Farthest\r\nRole\r\n  Artillery\r\nRole Size\r\n  Minion\r\nStance\r\n  Mindless\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nRumor tells of a hidden library with vast shelves of \r\nforgotten lore.  The party is given a few \r\n  rumors \r\nand a vague description of a location to go on, and \r\nasked to come back with a precise route to the place. \r\n  Quest Development\r\nA cultural puzzle presents itself, the solution to which \r\nmust be entered correctly on the first try or the \r\nobstacle and any treasure or information within is \r\ndestroyed.  The answer can be located in the deep lore \r\nof the city’s library, the search of which will take days.\r\n  Reward\r\nThe next time a member of the party learns a spell \r\nfrom a scroll or spellbook, that spell is not “consumed” \r\nand may be cast from the book or scroll afterwards as \r\nthough the learning had never taken place.\r\n  Penalty\r\nThe curse of undeath lingers about you for a fortnight.  \r\nEach foe felled rolls a \r\n  d20; on a 1, they rise in the \r\nmanner described above.  If they were already of the \r\nundead type, they rise on a 1-3.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Chase\r\nSub\r\n      Lost the Trail\r\n15"
