        "number": 13,
        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-3/13_icon.png",
        "description": "13\r\nCircular Pattern\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nPattern\r\nVerb\r\nRecur\r\nAdjective\r\nRepeated\r\nAdverb\r\nInevitably\r\nQuestion\r\nNo\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nNo; not until a cycle is broken \r\nor a routine is interrupted.\r\nSocial\r\nThe NPC rehashes a previously-discussed topic, and \r\ndoesn’t seem to remember their first stance on it.  It \r\ntakes successes to get them to clarify what they truly \r\nwant to convey, or to reroute them to another topic.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Ally\r\nContext\r\n  Lull in Fighting\r\nChoice\r\n  Mislead\r\nResult\r\n  Questions Motives\r\nCombat\r\nIf the enemy’s next attack roll hits, they receive an \r\nadditional bonus attack using the same attack bonus \r\nand with the same effects as that first attack.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nThe next time you would roll for a random encounter, \r\nyou instead face a group of NPCs or monsters that you \r\nfaced earlier in the campaign who were not destroyed.  \r\nIf none such applies, you run into relatives or faction \r\ncomrades of someone you have run into and triumphed \r\nover before.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Maneuver\r\nTargeting\r\n  Rearguard\r\nRole\r\n  Controller\r\nRole Size\r\n  Normal\r\nStance\r\n  Cornered\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nTake an item or escort someone to a destination, then \r\nreturn with another item or different person back to \r\nwhere you began.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nYour next objective requires you to disrupt, stop, \r\nprotect, or steal from a caravan along its regular route.\r\n  Reward\r\nThe next treasure you receive, select one category of \r\ntreasure obtained at random; the treasure of that type \r\nis doubled in quantity.  Rolls on treasure tables, and \r\nvalue, are unaffected.\r\n  Penalty\r\nThe next dungeon you enter will be a maze.  \r\nUse random direction generators and/or an \r\n  \r\nIntelligence save or check to determine whether and \r\nhow you’re able to escape.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Complex\r\nSub\r\n      1d4+1 Parallel\r\n16"
