        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-4/8_icon.png",
        "description": "8\r\nCathedral\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nSerenity\r\nVerb\r\nEnsconce\r\nAdjective\r\nSerene\r\nAdverb\r\nSerenely\r\nQuestion\r\nMaybe\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nIf it is willed to be so.\r\nSocial\r\nYou face a devout person whose zeal lies just \r\nbeneath the surface.  They take a hard line against \r\nanything that is not completely dedicated to their \r\nchurch (randomize which), and make thinly-veiled \r\nsuggestions as to what members of their faith feel \r\nabout those outside the congregation.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Opponent\r\nContext\r\n  Formal Gathering\r\nChoice\r\n  Intimidate\r\nResult\r\n  Can Grant Plot Clue\r\nCombat\r\nOne-third of the enemies, rounded up, are capable \r\nof divine spellcasting.  If they have class levels, they \r\nare in \r\n  Cleric; if they are monsters, their magical \r\nabilities are that of a Cleric of level equal to half the \r\nmonster’s hit dice.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nGenerate an NPC encounter; half the resulting NPCs \r\nare Clerics capable of divine spellcasting.  Their fervor \r\nmakes them absolutely certain that the PCs are acting \r\nagainst the interests of the church.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Ability\r\nTargeting\r\n  Strongest\r\nRole\r\n  Controller\r\nRole Size\r\n  Mindless\r\nStance\r\n  Overwhelmed\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nA local religious faction asks your assistance: venture \r\nto a far-flung iteration of their faith, and seek their \r\ncounsel.  The patron presenting the situation worries \r\nthat their local temple’s leadership has been infiltrated \r\nby evildoers, miscreants, or worse, and is themselves \r\nof insufficient station to investigate further without \r\nfear of reprisal.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nThe next item you seek is in the undercroft or secret \r\nchambers deep within a temple.\r\n  Reward\r\nYou gain the favor of a local church.  It does not affect \r\nyour membership in the faction or lack thereof, but \r\nyou may call upon any member of the church for a \r\nboon once.\r\n  Penalty\r\nA leader in a divine \r\n  faction sets their sights upon \r\nthe party, convinced that they are up to no good.  They \r\nact to thwart you until satisfied that you do not act \r\nagainst their interests.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Mystery\r\nSub\r\n  Whodunnit\r\n11"
