        "number": 11,
        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-4/11_icon.png",
        "description": "11\r\nCertification\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nVeracity\r\nVerb\r\nVerify\r\nAdjective\r\nVerified\r\nAdverb\r\nTruthfully\r\nQuestion\r\nYes\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nYes, with absolute certainty.\r\nSocial\r\nYour conversational adversary gains sudden insight.  \r\nThey treat all social check successes as critical \r\nsuccesses, and may re-roll one failed check during this \r\nencounter.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Asset\r\nContext\r\n  Formal Gathering\r\nChoice\r\n  Subject Info\r\nResult\r\n  Can Grant Plot Clue\r\nCombat\r\nYour enemy studies your movements, and correctly \r\npredicts your next move.  You suffer \r\n  disadvantage \r\non your attack rolls next round, and they gain \r\n  \r\nadvantage on saving throws against your effects until \r\ntheir next turn.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nA group of ruffians has been charged with their own \r\nquest: kill the PCs, and bring proof of their demise \r\nto their patron.  Whether this is a case of mistaken \r\nidentity, being in the wrong place at the wrong time, \r\nor maybe a legitimate assassination attempt arranged \r\nby someone truly against the party, is in question.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Use / Defend\r\nTargeting\r\n  Weakest\r\nRole\r\n  Lurker\r\nRole Size\r\n  Elite\r\nStance\r\n  Fresh\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nYou’re asked to study a work of art, and verify whether \r\nit is fake.  If you have no true talent in such matters, it \r\ncould be that you are being set up to fail and take the \r\nblame as an accomplice to a theft or forgery.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nYou automatically hear \r\n  1d4 \r\n  rumors from \r\nvarious NPCs throughout the day that all align with \r\nyour objectives in various active quests.  If they seem \r\ntoo good to be true, they might be: each has a \r\n  50% \r\nchance of being false.\r\n  Reward\r\nYou hear enough snippets of common lore and local \r\nidioms to pick up on things: the next \r\n  1d4 \r\n  \r\nrumors you hear, you are correctly able to determine \r\nthe veracity of.\r\n  Penalty\r\nYour attempts to integrate with the local culture are \r\nterribly poor—something that the locals gain much \r\nglee in taking advantage of.  The next \r\n  1d4 \r\n  \r\nrumors you hear, you incorrectly deduce the accuracy \r\nof.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Slay\r\nSub\r\n  Clear\r\n14"
