        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-4/34_icon.png",
        "description": "34\r\nHeart\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nBeloved\r\nVerb\r\nLove\r\nAdjective\r\nPassionate\r\nAdverb\r\nLovingly\r\nQuestion\r\nYes\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nYes, yes; a thousand times, yes.\r\nSocial\r\nLove is a crucial factor in the conversation.  This might \r\nbe love the NPC has for another, whom they seek to \r\nprotect with lies; or, a secret lover they hope is not \r\nrevealed; or perhaps, the NPC is simply attracted to \r\nthe PC with the highest \r\n  Charisma.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Ally\r\nContext\r\n  Long Rest\r\nChoice\r\n  Diplomacy\r\nResult\r\n  Answers Willingly\r\nCombat\r\nEnemies gain \r\n  advantage on all fear-based, mind-\r\naffecting, and/or morale saves for the remainder of the \r\nencounter.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nTwo NPCs have run away together; in pursuit are \r\nparties hired by both of their families.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Attack Main\r\nTargeting\r\n  Closest\r\nRole\r\n  Soldier\r\nRole Size\r\n  Normal\r\nStance\r\n  Fresh\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nThe party is asked to deliver a love letter.  Whether \r\nthat love is requited, appropriate, scandalous, secret, \r\nand/or or even lawful, are likely not things that the \r\nquest-giver or the NPCs involved want the party to \r\nknow.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nYour next obstacle involves someone deeply passionate \r\nabout blocking your progress.  Their justification \r\nand reasons may be righteous, and you might be \r\nsympathetic to their stance.\r\n  Reward\r\nLyrics and/or sheet music that, when played, double \r\nthe impact of a bard’s talents for one encounter, or \r\ngrant \r\n  advantage on a single Performance check of \r\nthe user’s choice.\r\n  Penalty\r\nAn NPC grows overly fond of one of the PCs.  While \r\nostensibly a good thing, they want only for that PC to \r\nretire from adventuring and spend time with them… \r\nand they have a way or interfering with the party if \r\nthis aim is refused.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Deliver\r\nSub\r\n  Escort\r\n53"
