        "number": 35,
        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-4/35_icon.png",
        "description": "35\r\nApple\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nFruitful\r\nVerb\r\nEat\r\nAdjective\r\nJuicy\r\nAdverb\r\nFruitfully\r\nQuestion\r\nNo\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nNo, but that is based on \r\nyour current knowledge and \r\nawareness—gaining insight \r\nmay cause you to rephrase the \r\nquestion and receive a different \r\nresult.\r\nSocial\r\nHunger strikes the NPC.  They need to eat in order to \r\ncontinue the conversation; failure to do so imposes \r\n  disadvantage on your social checks against them.  \r\nPerhaps this drives a change in venue; an opportunity \r\nto share rations; or if you’re already in a tavern or \r\nrestaurant, to summon a server.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Bystander\r\nContext\r\n  Short Rest\r\nChoice\r\n  Diplomacy\r\nResult\r\n  Answers Grudgingly\r\nCombat\r\nEnemy gains \r\n  advantage on ranged attack rolls \r\ntheir next turn.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nA villain poisons or curses the party’s foodstuffs while \r\nthey sleep or from afar with magic.  The next time they \r\n  rest, saving throws will determine if they suffer ill \r\neffects.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Attack Secondary\r\nTargeting\r\n  Ranged Enemy\r\nRole\r\n  Soldier\r\nRole Size\r\n  Normal\r\nStance\r\n  Fresh\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nLocate and obtain vital foodstuffs in service to hungry \r\nvillagers and/or desirous alchemists.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nStarvation becomes a complication: either the party’s \r\nrations are ruined or spoiled; an intermediary village \r\nor faction has their food stores poisoned or stolen; and \r\nso on.  This new issue must be addressed immediately, \r\nor the party may suffer consequences for ignoring it.\r\n  Reward\r\nSpecial rations that grant that extra spring in your \r\nstep and heightened spirit: once following your next \r\n  short or \r\n  long rest, you may choose to gain a +1 \r\nluck bonus to any one roll, declared before you attempt \r\nthe roll.\r\n  Penalty\r\nParty’s current rations spoil and are unusable.  They \r\nmay have to forage, barter, deal, or steal in order \r\nto feed themselves while they secure replacement \r\nfoodstuffs.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Obtain\r\nSub\r\n  Gather\r\n54"
