        "number": 21,
        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-5/21_icon.png",
        "description": "21\r\nAtomic\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nPiece\r\nVerb\r\nDash\r\nAdjective\r\nSmall\r\nAdverb\r\nMinutely\r\nQuestion\r\nMaybe\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nMaybe.  The situation is far too \r\nchaotic to be able to predict.\r\nSocial\r\nThe person is distracted by a seemingly small, \r\ninsignificant thing that feels unrelated to the \r\nconversation you’re trying to have… but this stance \r\nsubconsciously hiding a deeper connection?\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Opponent\r\nContext\r\n  Combat\r\nChoice\r\n  Intimidate\r\nResult\r\n  Turns Hostile\r\nCombat\r\nYour enemies ignore difficult terrain, and increase \r\ntheir base Speed in all movements by +50%, for \r\nthis combat.  They may also each reroll one failed \r\n  \r\nDexterity save this combat.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nRoll \r\n  1d4 random encounters; these occur in \r\nsuccession.  Although they seem truly and normally \r\nrandom, they turn out to all be related to each other.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Ability\r\nTargeting\r\n  Frontline\r\nRole\r\n  Artillery\r\nRole Size\r\n  Elite\r\nStance\r\n  Relentless\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nYou’re given a set of instructions that seems unrelated \r\nor contradictory, and chastised if you ask any \r\nquestions about the ultimate purpose behind the tasks.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nCreate a new quest entirely; this new quest must be \r\nresolved in full before you are able to progress with \r\none of your active quests.\r\n  Reward\r\nA crude map that nevertheless provides insight into \r\nthe positions of enemies; you may use this to avoid \r\none random combat encounter, or to locate one group \r\nof creatures or NPCs in the region.  The map is useful \r\nonly for the next two days.\r\n  Penalty\r\nEnemies have become aware of the party’s position \r\nand nature; rolls to determine whether a random \r\nencounter takes place suffer \r\n  disadvantage, and the \r\nenemy gains \r\n  advantage on \r\n  Surprise checks.  \r\nThis effect lasts for two days.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Complex\r\nSub\r\n      1d4+1 Sequential\r\n32"
