        "number": 9,
        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-6/9_icon.png",
        "description": "9\r\nConcoction\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nPotion\r\nVerb\r\nConcoct\r\nAdjective\r\nBubbly\r\nAdverb\r\nEnthusiastically\r\nQuestion\r\nMaybe\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nMaybe; there are many chaotic \r\nforces at work.\r\nSocial\r\nAmidst the conversation, the NPC has a drink.  The \r\nact is innocuous, but the contents are not: they fall \r\nunder the influence of a random potion-appropriate \r\nspell (invisibility, fly, sleep, spider climb, etc.).  It’s \r\nnot immediately clear whether someone has interfered \r\nwith their beverage, or if their magical action is \r\nintentional, perhaps to escape conversation?\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Opponent\r\nContext\r\n  Informal Gathering\r\nChoice\r\n  Mislead\r\nResult\r\n  Red Herring\r\nCombat\r\nEach enemy produces a potion that would aid their \r\ncombat position most (healing, fly, haste, etc.) and \r\ndrinks it. \r\n  Random Encounter\r\nYou come across a treasure which seems to be \r\n  2d4 \r\nmagical potions that are of immediate benefit to your \r\ncircumstances.  However, each one actually produces \r\na random potion effect which could be beneficial or \r\nharmful.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Attack Secondary\r\nTargeting\r\n  Frontline\r\nRole\r\n  Controller\r\nRole Size\r\n  Elite\r\nStance\r\n  Bloodied\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nGather ingredients to make a special potion.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nTo pass by an obstacle on your way to your next \r\nquest objective, you must combine ingredients or \r\nenvironmental elements to produce a solution.  This \r\ncould be an engineering or physics solution involving \r\nstacked logs, or brewing a potion made of local \r\ningredients.\r\n  Reward\r\n  2d6 random potions.\r\n  Penalty\r\n  1d4 of the potions currently carried by the party \r\n(randomly select which ones) spoil or leak, and are \r\nuseless.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Obtain\r\nSub\r\n  Find\r\n12"
