        "oracleSet": 6,
        "number": 11,
        "imagePath": "/oracle-images/oracle-6/11_icon.png",
        "description": "11\r\nGraph\r\nGeneral\r\nNoun\r\nMeasurement\r\nVerb\r\nMeasure\r\nAdjective\r\nMeasured\r\nAdverb\r\nSpecifically\r\nQuestion\r\nMaybe\r\nDetailed \r\nAnswer\r\nMaybe, but if there is ever \r\ncertainty, you will be able to \r\ndetect it immediately.\r\nSocial\r\nKeep track of successes and failures.  After 5 successes, \r\nyou gain a better \r\n  Attitude by one step from your \r\nNPC conversation partner.  After 5 failures, their \r\nAttitude toward you degrades one step.  Each success \r\nthey score in the conversation counts as a failure; \r\nsimilarly, each failure they suffer counts as a success.  \r\nKeep track of all of this in secret and roleplay the \r\nimpact, if any.\r\nSocial\r\nRole\r\n  Bystander\r\nContext\r\n  Lull in Fighting\r\nChoice\r\n  Diplomacy\r\nResult\r\n  Can Grant Plot Clue\r\nCombat\r\nRoll a \r\n  d6.  After that many attacks (made by the \r\nparty or the enemy), the next attack roll gains \r\n  \r\nadvantage.  Then, roll another \r\n  d6; after that many \r\nattacks, the next attack roll suffers \r\n  disadvantage.  \r\nRepeat for the entire combat encounter.  Keep track of \r\nthese rolls in secret and reveal the impact on a die roll \r\nonly just as it is about to be made.\r\n  Random Encounter\r\nRoll \r\n  1d4 times on the appropriate random \r\nencounter table; ignore noncombat results; all of the \r\nresulting enemies appear at once.\r\nCombat\r\nOutcome\r\n  Use / Defend\r\nTargeting\r\n  Rearguard\r\nRole\r\n  Controller\r\nRole Size\r\n  Normal\r\nStance\r\n  Fresh\r\nQuest & Encounter\r\n  New Quest\r\nScout a region, and report back on the numbers and \r\nlocations of enemies and monsters.\r\n  Quest Development\r\nYou must gather specific amounts of \r\n  2d4 different \r\nkids of items.  This, toward an alchemical creation; an \r\narcane incantation; a divine ritual; and/or to satisfy \r\nthe more worldly needs of a bribed official, noble, or \r\nmerchant.\r\n  Reward\r\nThe next time you approach a shop with the intent to \r\nsell, they will buy what you have for \r\n  75% of its \r\nnormal value instead of the regular 50%. \r\n  Penalty\r\nPrices in nearby towns skyrocket.  They will buy from \r\nyou only at \r\n  25% of normal value, but everything \r\nthey sell is 50% more expensive.  This effect lasts a \r\nfortnight.\r\nQuest\r\nArchetype\r\n  Obtain\r\nSub\r\n  Fetch\r\n14"
